FBIS3-21131 "jpjst008__l94001" JPRS-JST-94-008-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Science & Technology Japan 2 March 1994 Science & Technology Policy/Economic Competitiveness Sumitomo Lab To Conduct Micromachine R&D 94P60108 Tokyo NIKKAN KOGYO SHIMBUN in Japanese p 9--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY 94P60108 Tokyo NIKKAN KOGYO SHIMBUN Language: Japanese Article Type:CSO [Text] Sumitomo Electric Industries Ltd. (Noritaka Kurauchi, president) held a ceremony opening its Haruma Laboratory built at the Haruma Science City in western Hyogo Prefecture. The laboratory, with its superconducting, small-scale ``NIJI-III'' SOR (synchrotron orbit radiation) device, will conduct R&D on precision machining for micromachines as well as such topics as new materials and funtionally gradient materials. The laboratory is built on a two-hectacre industrial site (in Kamigori, Hyogo Prefecture) obtained from Hyogo Prefecture. The total cost of building the lab came to Â¥5 billion.
